Quote: On Saturday mornings at the lively Frankton market in Hamilton, a Fijian man sells large bottles containing the distilled juice of the nonu fruit, also known as noni... Nonu/noni, botanical name <i>Morinda citrifolia</i>, has been part of any Pacific healer's treatment kit for many hundreds of years, whereas kava (from the plant <i>Piper methysticum</i>) is the base of a drink consumed on both ritual and social occasions.
